error[expander::invalid-binding-name]: Invalid binding name
  ╭▸ 
3 │ ["::kernel::special_form::type", "::x", { "#literal": 1 }, "x"]
  │                                   ━━━ expected a type name for the `type` binding
  │
  ├ help: write `(type Name type-expr body)` with a name like `MyType` or `Pair<A, B>`
  ╰ note: the first argument to `type` introduces a new type alias and must be a simple identifier, optionally with generic parameters